                <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/201: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Mission at Lausanne</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="69" xml:id="d259fn69">The Ambassador in Italy (Child) and the Minister
                        in Switzerland (Grew) had been instructed to be present at Lausanne as
                        observers during the sessions of the conference for negotiating peace
                        between the Allies and Turkey.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lausanne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-26T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1922—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 26, 10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. The Allies control the agenda and order of bringing up subjects for
                    consideration and are manipulating this advantage. Questions relating to
                    Mesopotamia are imminent and urgent. There is reason to believe that the policy
                    of Great Britain, backed by the general attitude of the Conservatives in
                    England, may be to seek withdrawal from Mesopotamia in return for advantages
                    with respect to concessions, especially in the matter of petroleum. Instructions
                    concerning definite arrangements are now lacking, but are necessary at once if
                    we are to safeguard American interests adequately. We feel that with such
                    instructions we might be able to give protection to American interests outside
                    of Conference meetings instead of being placed in the position of entering a
                    protest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
